               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85043024">
                  <summary>1 copy of Maʻlūmāt al-āfāq by Amīn al-Dīn Khān Haravī</summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1547-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Maʻlūmāt al-āfāq (Knowledge of the Horizons), an illustrated geography by Amīn al-Dīn Khān ibn Sayyid Abū al-Makārim Amīr Khān Ḥusaynī Haravī on the seven climes, their marvels and natural products and including a gazetteer of the principal towns. Mention of the Emperor Aurangzeb as deceased gives a date of composition of after 1707 (See Storey, Persian Literature II, p. 142 and Simon Digby, “Beyond the Ocean: Perceptions of Overseas in Indo-Persian Sources of the Mughal Period”, Studies in History 15.2 ns (1999), pp. 256-8).</p>
                        <p>Preceded by a list of contents (ff. 1v-4r). Profusely illustrated.</p>
                        <p>ff. 189; 15 lines per page; nastaʻliq; rubrications; ruled margins; ill.; dated 28 Sha’ban 1226 (17 Sep. 1811)</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f3658">Amīn al-Dīn Khān Haravī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f3658">امین الدین خان هروی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_4558">Maʻlūmāt al-āfāq</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_4558">معلومات الآفاق</title>
                  </msItem>
